{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "kjva:sirach.30",
    "translationId": "kjva",
    "bookSlug": "sirach",
    "chapterNumber": 30,
    "referenceLabel": "Sirach 30",
    "summary": "Source text for Sirach 30 in King James Version with Apocrypha."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.30.1",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 30:1",
      "text": "He that loveth his son causeth him oft to feel the rod, that he may have joy of him in the end.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.30.2",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 30:2",
      "text": "He that chastiseth his son shall have joy in him, and shall rejoice of him among his acquaintance.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.30.3",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 30:3",
      "text": "He that teacheth his son grieveth the enemy: and before his friends he shall rejoice of him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.30.4",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 30:4",
      "text": "Though his father die, yet he is as though he were not dead: for he hath left one behind him that is like himself.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.30.5",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 30:5",
      "text": "While he lived, he saw and rejoiced in him: and when he died, he was not sorrowful.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.30.6",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 30:6",
      "text": "He left behind him an avenger against his enemies, and one that shall requite kindness to his friends.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.30.7",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 30:7",
      "text": "He that maketh too much of his son shall bind up his wounds; and his bowels will be troubled at every cry.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.30.8",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 30:8",
      "text": "An horse not broken becometh headstrong: and a child left to himself will be wilful.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.30.9",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 30:9",
      "text": "Cocker thy child, and he shall make thee afraid: play with him, and he will bring thee to heaviness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.30.10",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 30:10",
      "text": "Laugh not with him, lest thou have sorrow with him, and lest thou gnash thy teeth in the end.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.30.11",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 30:11",
      "text": "Give him no liberty in his youth, and wink not at his follies.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.30.12",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 30:12",
      "text": "Bow down his neck while he is young, and beat him on the sides while he is a child, lest he wax stubborn, and be disobedient unto thee, and so bring sorrow to thine heart.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.30.13",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 30:13",
      "text": "Chastise thy son, and hold him to labour, lest his lewd behaviour be an offence unto thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.30.14",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 30:14",
      "text": "Better is the poor, being sound and strong of constitution, than a rich man that is afflicted in his body.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.30.15",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 30:15",
      "text": "Health and good estate of body are above all gold, and a strong body above infinite wealth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.30.16",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 30:16",
      "text": "There is no riches above a sound body, and no joy above the joy of the heart.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.30.17",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 30:17",
      "text": "Death is better than a bitter life or continual sickness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.30.18",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 30:18",
      "text": "Delicates poured upon a mouth shut up are as messes of meat set upon a grave.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.30.19",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 30:19",
      "text": "What good doeth the offering unto an idol? for neither can it eat nor smell: so is he that is persecuted of the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.30.20",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 30:20",
      "text": "He seeth with his eyes and groaneth, as an eunuch that embraceth a virgin and sigheth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.30.21",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 30:21",
      "text": "Give not over thy mind to heaviness, and afflict not thyself in thine own counsel.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.30.22",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 30:22",
      "text": "The gladness of the heart is the life of man, and the joyfulness of a man prolongeth his days.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.30.23",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 30:23",
      "text": "Love thine own soul, and comfort thy heart, remove sorrow far from thee: for sorrow hath killed many, and there is no profit therein.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.30.24",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 30:24",
      "text": "Envy and wrath shorten the life, and carefulness bringeth age before the time.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.30.25",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 30:25",
      "text": "A cheerful and good heart will have a care of his meat and diet.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
